5:
Thanks for everything today, Will. If
you come up with any new
inventions, I'd love to see them.
25:
I never thought I'd have this kind of
relationship with Will... Am I
dreaming?
31:
...IT'S NOT ENOUGH! THIS GIRL NEEDS
MORE LOVING, WILL!
36: That's all for today. See you later.
41:
Yup. Good cake here, we should
come back some time.
45:
B-but come on! We're dating, aren't
we? I've been waiting ages for this!
50:
But it's like our relationship hasn't
changed at all since childhood!
59:
...W-well, we're holding hands a lot
more now...
64:
If you're gonna brag, just get it over
with already.
69:
B-but just holding hands isn't
enough! I want to do things that...
lovers do!
72:
I wanna hug him... And I, um... Maybe
k-kiss, sometimes...
76:
B-but really! Don't you think it's
about time Will made a move? Do
you think he even wants to?!
80:
He's probably just chickening out
like before.
90:
What are you still afraid of? Stop
overthinking everything and just go
for it.
94:
...I'm worried he might not like it if I'm
too aggressive, though...
100:
So you're just leaving it all up to him,
then. Nice.
104:
You're the last person I want to hear
that from!
108:
You're not holding back anymore,
are you?
112:
Would Will not like it if you tried to
hug and kiss him?
117:
I don't think he'd be too against it at
first, but Will's the sort of person to
act nice even if he's not really into
something.
121:
You've really been mulling over it,
huh.
133:
I want him to know how I feel... but I
don't want to push it too hard.
138:
...Well, understanding each other's
boundaries is very important when
establishing physical contact in a
relationship.
142:
Yeah, I guess... You have a point
there.
146:
I understand the uneasiness of not
wanting to burden the other person
with your feelings.
154:
Reticia? You seem... pretty serious
about this...
158:
But you can't have a relationship
without trusting each other, either.
Mutual care for each other's feelings
is crucial.
161:
First off, perhaps it's best to see how
he reacts to physical touch. Just
take it one step at a time though,
okay?
165:
...Yeah, okay. I do want to make sure
we're on the same page...
168:
But then... What's a good way of
checking his boundaries?
195:
*sigh* What should I do... I don't
want to push things too hard...
203:
W-Will? What're you doing here?
Didn't you have work today?
207:
Yeah, but I'm all finished with the
sheep now. I'm just headed home.
210:
...But I'm glad I got to see you. I was
just thinking about you, actually.
213:
Are you headed home too? I'll walk
you there—
218:
H-hey, Will. I've got something I want
to ask you!
221:
After I... confessed to you the other
day...
224:
When I hugged you... Were you, um,
fine with that?
238:
I want to hug you right now, if you'd
like that...
247:
Th-thank you! Sorry for how sudden
that was, but I'm all good now!
249:
Oh! But Will, if you ever wanna do
something with me... I'd be down for
anything, you know?
